symbols.name: ol.WEBGL_MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE
symbols.description:
The maximum supported WebGL texture size in pixels. If WebGL is not
supported, the value is set to `undefined`.

symbols.name: ol.inherits

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_CANVAS
defines.description:
Enable the Canvas renderer.  Default is `true`. Setting
    this to false at compile time in advanced mode removes all code
    supporting the Canvas renderer from the build.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_DOM
defines.description:
Enable the DOM renderer (used as a fallback where Canvas is
    not available).  Default is `true`. Setting this to false at compile time
    in advanced mode removes all code supporting the DOM renderer from the
    build.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_IMAGE
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Image based layers.  Default
    is `true`. Setting this to false at compile time in advanced mode removes
    all code supporting Image layers from the build.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_NAMED_COLORS
defines.description:
Enable Closure named colors (`goog.color.names`).
    Enabling these colors adds about 3KB uncompressed / 1.5KB compressed to
    the final build size.  Default is `false`. This setting has no effect
    with Canvas renderer, which uses its own names, whether this is true or
    false.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_PROJ4JS
defines.description:
Enable integration with the Proj4js library.  Default is
    `true`.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_TILE
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Tile based layers.  Default is
    `true`. Setting this to false at compile time in advanced mode removes
    all code supporting Tile layers from the build.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_VECTOR
defines.description:
Enable rendering of ol.layer.Vector based layers.  Default
    is `true`. Setting this to false at compile time in advanced mode removes
    all code supporting Vector layers from the build.

defines.name: ol.ENABLE_WEBGL
defines.description:
Enable the WebGL renderer.  Default is `true`. Setting
    this to false at compile time in advanced mode removes all code
    supporting the WebGL renderer from the build.

defines.name: ol.LEGACY_IE_SUPPORT
defines.description:
Support legacy IE (7-8).  Default is `false`.
    If set to `true`, `goog.array.ASSUME_NATIVE_FUNCTIONS` must be set
    to `false` because legacy IE do not support ECMAScript 5 array functions.
